org.greatage.ioc
Interface Contributor<T>

Type Parameters:
T - service type
All Known Implementing Classes:
ContributorImpl
public interface Contributor<T>

This class represents service contribution definition that distributively configures services. By default it is configured by module contribute methods annotated with Contribute class.

Since:
1.0
Author:
Ivan Khalopik

Checks if this service contribution definition supports specified service.

Parameters:

Returns:
true if this service configuration definition supports specified service, false otherwise

contribute

void contribute(ServiceResources<T> resources)
Contributes to service configuration using service resource. It manipulates with three types of service configuration: Configuration, OrderedConfiguration and MappedConfiguration and provides collection, list and map to service via ServiceResources respectively.

Parameters:
resources - service resources
